text: Marianne Claire Dew (born 1938), is a female former athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== She represented England in the 220 yards at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. She won a silver medal at the 1958 European Athletics Championships. ==References== Category:1938 births Category:English female sprinters Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
